    "reason": "Bound the `.preflight-confirmed` stamp to `sha256(scripts.json)` plus a 60-min default TTL. New `confirm-batch` subcommand on `tools/sample_matrix_run.py` is the single writer; the bash hook recomputes the hash via `sha256sum`/`shasum -a 256` and rejects on mismatch, missing JSON, or TTL expiry — closing the three drift modes the issue called out (regenerated scripts post-confirm, fresh-checkout stamp reuse, two-batches-in-progress cross-talk). Updated `/run-batch`, CLAUDE.md, and README.md to use the new command, and rewrote tests/suites/40-preflight-hook.sh + added tests/suites/55-confirm-batch.sh (round-trips a Python-written stamp through the bash hook to catch hash-recipe drift in CI).",
